### 6. Compute Value Model Documentation + Exchange Page as Tool

**Problem:** The compute value model (~120 lines: philosophy, reference hardware, performance, operating cost, multi-GPU scaling, transaction fees, peg rationale, long-term vision) only existed as inline copy on `exchange.html`. The page was half documentation, half tool — a user coming to bridge ETH had to scroll past 6 documentation cards before reaching the bridge form. No standalone doc existed for node operators, integrators, or linking.

**Fix:** Moved all documentation content into standalone markdown, linked from the exchange page:

- **New doc** `docs/getting-started/ait-value-model.md` covering all sections (what AIT represents, €0.25 reference, reference hardware, performance, operating cost breakdown, multi-GPU scaling table, transaction fees, why-not-peg, long-term vision, cross-links)
- **Exchange page reworked** — removed 6 inline documentation cards (121 lines), replaced with a single "How AIT Is Valued" card containing GitHub DOC links. Page is now: value hero → live price ticker → bridge form → track deposit → bridges link → early adopter CTA → value-model doc links → API endpoints. Tool first, documentation one click away.
- **GitHub links** — both doc links point to `https://github.com/oib/AITBC/blob/main/docs/getting-started/...` with `target="_blank" rel="noopener"`
- **Landing page** — added "AIT Value Model" DOC link to Documentation card

**Files changed:**
- `docs/getting-started/ait-value-model.md` — **new** doc (all documentation content moved from exchange.html)
- `website/exchange.html` — removed 6 documentation cards, added "How AIT Is Valued" card with GitHub DOC links
- `website/index.html` — added AIT Value Model DOC link to Documentation card

